            <p class="eyebrow">Service overview</p>
            <h2>What root intrusion repair actually solves</h2>
            <p>Roots do not break a healthy sewer. They find a hairline crack, a misaligned joint, or a missing seal and grow inward toward the water and nutrients. Cleaning them out helps for a few months; repairing the entry point is the only permanent fix.</p><p>Honest Drain locates the intrusion with a camera and a sonde, then chooses between a spot repair on a single joint, a longer section replacement, or a referral to a trenchless contractor when conditions favor that approach.</p>
            <p class="link-row"><a class="text-link" href="../../../contact.html">Book a service visit</a></p>
